WEBVTT

00:01.250 --> 00:02.625
(narrator)
Previously on "Hellcats.."

00:02.625 --> 00:04.250
You sure school's
worth all this?

00:04.250 --> 00:06.875
Dan, I'm going to graduate,
pass the bar up North

00:06.875 --> 00:08.542
and work in the DA's office
where everybody talks

00:08.542 --> 00:10.625
in flat Yankee vowels.

00:10.625 --> 00:12.000
Mom, what is this?

00:12.000 --> 00:14.000
It says
my scholarship was canceled.

00:14.000 --> 00:16.167
Tighten up!

00:16.167 --> 00:17.209
[all screaming]

00:18.000 --> 00:20.375
Six weeks?
I'll miss qualifiers.

00:20.375 --> 00:22.000
You're applying
for a scholarship?

00:22.000 --> 00:24.209
I have one now
for cheerleading.

00:24.209 --> 00:25.834
Cheerleading?

00:30.250 --> 00:32.333
- Oh.
- Hello, Marti.

00:32.333 --> 00:34.208
- Welcome to Cheer Town.
- I voted against you.

00:34.208 --> 00:37.000
- Democracy's a bitch.
- Apparently, so are you.

00:37.000 --> 00:40.084
Vanessa, I'm sure you remember
the famous coach Red Raymond?

00:40.084 --> 00:42.417
Just so we're clear,
I have a boyfriend.

00:42.417 --> 00:43.667
Things change.

00:43.667 --> 00:45.000
The Hellcats
are short on flyers

00:45.000 --> 00:46.167
at a crucial moment.

00:46.167 --> 00:48.125
Come Sunday,
you'll get bounced.

00:48.125 --> 00:50.125
I was a gymnast
up until high school.

00:50.125 --> 00:52.875
My mom was screaming
and hooting and hollering.

00:52.875 --> 00:55.084
I'd feel
her soul-sucking presence

00:55.084 --> 00:57.333
get wigged out
and fail the routine.

00:57.333 --> 00:59.875
You must be really
excited about seeing
Marti at qualifiers.

00:59.875 --> 01:01.500
It would be fun
to surprise her.

01:01.500 --> 01:03.291
Uh, your boyfriend's welcome,
of course.

01:03.291 --> 01:06.042
What? Dan?
Oh, no, we're just buds.

01:07.959 --> 01:10.000
[crowd cheering]

01:10.000 --> 01:13.291
[theme music]

01:16.000 --> 01:19.291
[instrumental music]

01:24.875 --> 01:27.333
Oh, what have I
gotten myself into?

01:27.333 --> 01:29.917
The best experience ever
in life.

01:29.917 --> 01:33.125
(Vanessa)
Circle up, Hellcats!

01:33.125 --> 01:34.625
Do you feel it?

01:34.625 --> 01:37.125
Do you feel the weight?

01:37.125 --> 01:39.625
Today one squad
will qualify for regionals.

01:39.625 --> 01:44.291
No one in their right mind
thinks it's gonna be us.

01:44.291 --> 01:48.333
The university,
they've given us an ultimatum.

01:48.333 --> 01:52.084
Place at Nationals
or they will gut our program.

01:52.084 --> 01:53.583
Are you feeling the weight?

01:55.875 --> 01:57.209
[chuckles]

01:57.209 --> 01:59.041
Well, I'm not.

01:59.041 --> 02:01.458
I'm light as a feather

02:01.458 --> 02:05.125
because you are
champions of the spirit.

02:05.125 --> 02:07.209
You ignore the scoreboard.

02:07.209 --> 02:09.667
Long odds are irrelevant.

02:09.667 --> 02:13.375
'In the face of seemingly
insurmountable adversity'

02:13.375 --> 02:16.167
'you do not waiver.'

02:16.167 --> 02:19.708
You roll, you tumble..

02:19.708 --> 02:21.167
...you fly.

02:21.167 --> 02:22.417
[all cheering]

02:22.417 --> 02:23.959
Punch it!

02:23.959 --> 02:25.708
(all)
Hellcats!

02:33.667 --> 02:35.708
[instrumental music]

02:37.208 --> 02:40.209
First competition.
Exciting, huh?

02:41.000 --> 02:44.209
It's, uh...something.

02:44.209 --> 02:47.000
- Who're those guys?
- Memphis Christian.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.125
'The team to beat.'

02:49.125 --> 02:51.166
Not much for showing the skin,
are they?

02:51.166 --> 02:53.667
Well, Mem-Chris
is a religious school.

02:53.667 --> 02:56.500
Jesus is the wind
beneath their skirts.

02:57.917 --> 03:00.291
Savannah went there before
she transferred to Lancer.

03:04.166 --> 03:06.291
Charlotte,
I want to wish you luck.

03:09.083 --> 03:11.125
I heard Alice got hurt.

03:12.042 --> 03:13.209
Yeah, but we got
this new girl.

03:13.209 --> 03:15.250
- Marti.
- Yeah, I saw her.

03:15.250 --> 03:16.375
She's a moose.

03:16.375 --> 03:18.000
We're going to bury you,
so you should

03:18.000 --> 03:19.792
probably keep that luck
for yourself.

03:19.792 --> 03:23.667
- I don't believe in it.
- Still...I wish you the best.

03:25.750 --> 03:28.834
Okay, Cyclones, let's run that
again, like you mean it!

03:28.834 --> 03:31.041
'Five, six, seven, eight!'

03:33.041 --> 03:35.209
What'd Charlotte have to say?

03:35.959 --> 03:37.708
She wished us luck.

03:38.875 --> 03:39.959
[screaming]

03:39.959 --> 03:41.583
Oh, I'll be back.

03:41.583 --> 03:43.291
'Yo, Dan Patch!'

03:45.375 --> 03:47.583
You look amazing,
despite the fact

03:47.583 --> 03:49.583
that you're dressed
like a cheerleader.

03:49.583 --> 03:52.042
- That part's weird.
- It's not weird,
it's perverse.

03:52.042 --> 03:53.917
Been missing your fly moves
at Empire.

03:53.917 --> 03:56.291
- You seduced Rosalie?
- I tried.

03:56.291 --> 03:59.125
Ended up making sweet love
to myself by mistake.

03:59.125 --> 04:01.291
- Happens to the best of us.
- What can I say, you know?

04:01.291 --> 04:04.250
I need my wing woman
to keep my head on straight.

04:04.250 --> 04:05.834
Well, I've been studying
like a   banshee

04:05.834 --> 04:08.125
and training 24-7
for this thing.

04:08.125 --> 04:11.875
When things settle down,
you know, my time
will free up.

04:11.875 --> 04:13.750
Hey, you want to come
and hang with us?

04:13.750 --> 04:15.084
Sitting with
the cheerleaders?

04:15.084 --> 04:18.333
- Yeah.
- Lordy, am I even allowed?

04:19.291 --> 04:21.791
I'm new.
We'll just plead ignorance.

04:21.791 --> 04:24.000
(man on radio)
'Marti Perkins
to convention security.'

04:24.000 --> 04:26.000
'Marti Perkins to security.'

04:26.000 --> 04:27.125
Yeah.

04:27.125 --> 04:30.000
Don't you understand?

04:30.000 --> 04:32.875
This is her
first cheer competition ever

04:32.875 --> 04:35.291
and she wants her mom here
for support

04:35.291 --> 04:37.000
but I can't let her know
I'm here

04:37.000 --> 04:39.083
if you don't let me backstage.

04:39.083 --> 04:40.917
Ma'am, we've paged
your daughter

04:40.917 --> 04:42.625
and she should be here
any minute.

04:42.625 --> 04:44.041
- Mom?
- Baby!

04:44.041 --> 04:46.042
Oh, I am so excited
to be here.

04:46.042 --> 04:48.625
I hope no one mistakes me
for a Hellcat.

04:48.625 --> 04:50.291
What are you doing here?
How did you find out
about this?

04:50.291 --> 04:53.250
Alice invited me,
but she's got me
sitting in the stands

04:53.250 --> 04:56.875
and I really think that
I should be backstage
with you.

04:56.875 --> 04:58.959
So would you
let this lady here

04:58.959 --> 05:00.792
know that it's okay
to let me through?

05:00.792 --> 05:02.166
Is there a problem?

05:03.250 --> 05:05.708
No problem.
Mom, you cannot be here.

05:07.458 --> 05:09.167
Why is Dan here?

05:10.875 --> 05:14.208
I'm-I'm dating
this cheerleader here.

05:14.208 --> 05:16.500
Baby, you look fine tonight.

05:17.583 --> 05:18.875
Okay, we're leaving.

05:18.875 --> 05:21.042
- I just got here!
- Now! Come on! We..

05:24.166 --> 05:25.875
Why did you say
we were dating?

05:25.875 --> 05:28.166
I was just taking
the heat off Marti.

05:28.166 --> 05:33.000
- It was a joke.
- Oh. I sometimes miss those.

05:33.000 --> 05:34.500
Anyway, you're Dan, right?

05:34.500 --> 05:36.792
- I'm Savannah Monroe.
- Yeah, charmed.

05:36.792 --> 05:39.542
I'm short on time, so please
keep your answers concise.

05:39.542 --> 05:42.208
You know Marti better
than I do. How much
trouble are we in?

05:42.208 --> 05:44.209
There was a scene
back in high school.

05:44.209 --> 05:46.083
Uh, her mom showed up
at a gymnastics event drunk--

05:46.083 --> 05:47.959
And vomited on her.
Yes, yes, I know all that.

05:47.959 --> 05:49.209
