♪ Ba-ba-da ba-ba-da ♪

14:58.417 --> 15:00.000
[clears throat]

15:09.458 --> 15:12.166
♪ Ba-ba-da ba-ba-da
ba-ba-da-ba-ba ♪

15:12.166 --> 15:15.250
♪ Ba-ba-da ba-ba-da
ba-ba-da-ba-ba ♪

15:15.250 --> 15:18.625
♪ Ba-ba-da ba-ba-da
ba-ba-da-ba-ba ♪

15:18.625 --> 15:21.250
♪ Things can't get
much worse ♪

15:23.208 --> 15:25.209
You talked to Wanda
since the incident?

15:26.083 --> 15:28.000
No time.

15:28.000 --> 15:29.667
And I felt kind of bad.

15:29.667 --> 15:31.959
I really bit her head off.

15:31.959 --> 15:34.625
- You need help
hiding the body?
- Nah, she regenerates.

15:36.083 --> 15:38.625
She means well. I mean..

15:38.625 --> 15:40.333
She doesn't wanna
make my life miserable.

15:40.333 --> 15:42.209
Yeah, it just kinda
works out that way.

15:42.209 --> 15:43.917
Manifest destiny.

15:43.917 --> 15:47.167
You know,
it takes two to tango.

15:48.875 --> 15:51.125
That is true.

15:51.125 --> 15:54.375
And when she's around,
I, I snap into caretaker mode

15:54.375 --> 15:56.458
and I can't help it,
so that's on me.

15:56.458 --> 15:58.667
No, but it doesn't matter
whose fault it is.

15:58.667 --> 16:00.875
See, the end result
is always the same.

16:00.875 --> 16:02.750
Wanda makes a scene,
and I end up

16:02.750 --> 16:04.625
blowing the spelling bee
or taking my driver's test.

16:04.625 --> 16:08.125
Or face planting
off the uneven parallel bars.

16:08.125 --> 16:09.917
[scoffs]

16:09.917 --> 16:11.042
You know what I need?

16:12.000 --> 16:13.875
- Space.
- From Wanda?

16:13.875 --> 16:15.625
- Yeah.
- Huh!

16:15.625 --> 16:19.000
- Good luck to you.
- Just a grace period.

16:19.000 --> 16:21.166
Until I can get this whole
schedule thing under control.

16:21.166 --> 16:23.125
It's teaching a pig to sing.

16:23.125 --> 16:24.708
It doesn't work
and it annoys the pig.

16:24.708 --> 16:26.834
- Oh, I love pig metaphors.
- Yeah.

16:26.834 --> 16:28.291
Now, can we, like,
slap some lipstick on it

16:28.291 --> 16:29.959
maybe cut off its ear
and make a silk purse?

16:29.959 --> 16:32.834
Okay, family goes
where it goes.
You can't control it.

16:32.834 --> 16:36.084
Hell, ever since James Jr.
and I moved back home
to help out

16:36.084 --> 16:37.542
we got six brothers
and sisters

16:37.542 --> 16:40.333
my dad, and his dad
all under one roof.

16:40.333 --> 16:41.917
There you go,
being Irish and all.

16:41.917 --> 16:43.917
It's a war zone. Yeah.

16:43.917 --> 16:45.208
You know,
we're tripping over ourselves

16:45.208 --> 16:46.500
getting in each other's way

16:46.500 --> 16:50.458
but...I guess if you
just sit back and you..

16:50.458 --> 16:52.167
...accept the messiness..

16:53.291 --> 16:55.209
...you can have
an excellent time.

16:55.209 --> 16:58.208
You know, I'm really
glad this whole Zen-master
serenity thing

16:58.208 --> 17:02.042
is working for you, Dan Patch,
but it's not an option for me.

17:03.750 --> 17:05.541
I'll still help you
hide the body.

17:06.333 --> 17:08.041
Do appreciate that.

17:08.041 --> 17:11.084
[instrumental music]

17:15.250 --> 17:17.250
[door closes]

17:19.041 --> 17:21.290
- Um, Marti--
- I am so glad
this day is over.

17:21.290 --> 17:22.750
- Marti--
- Oh, wait, it's not.

17:22.750 --> 17:24.290
I have four hours
of reading to do

17:24.290 --> 17:25.834
and a paper
on constitutional law.

17:25.834 --> 17:28.166
- What?
- You've got a visitor.

17:29.875 --> 17:31.583
She brought ribs.

17:36.084 --> 17:37.792
Mom?

17:37.792 --> 17:40.458
Why are you here?
Oh, and you brought food.

17:40.458 --> 17:43.458
The ribs are from Cozy Corner,
your favorite.

17:43.458 --> 17:46.291
- Mm-hmm.
- All is forgiven. Come here.

17:52.125 --> 17:54.959
I mean to tell you, we were
starting to get funny looks.

17:54.959 --> 17:58.125
And he really did
look like a hippie.

17:58.125 --> 18:01.291
So I told him,
if he wanted to see me again

18:01.291 --> 18:03.084
he had to lose
the soul patch.

18:03.084 --> 18:04.291
[chuckles]
And..

18:04.291 --> 18:07.708
Mm, so he shows up
an hour later.

18:07.708 --> 18:10.458
Face is smooth
as a baby's bottom

18:10.458 --> 18:12.250
and he bought
the shaving cream with him.

18:12.250 --> 18:13.917
[all laughing]

18:13.917 --> 18:15.834
- Classic.
- Who wants more corn bread?

18:15.834 --> 18:18.625
- She's actually fitting in.
- I'd give it time.

18:19.250 --> 18:20.583
So what about y'all?

18:20.583 --> 18:23.708
Any good dish
in the romance department?

18:23.708 --> 18:27.083
You know, I have
to imagine that a family
like the Hellcats

18:27.083 --> 18:29.125
can get a little
bit incestuous.

18:29.125 --> 18:30.583
Yeah, you got that right

18:30.583 --> 18:32.959
and the word goes
to Lewis and Alice.

18:32.959 --> 18:37.208
Well, my advice to you
is to stick with it

18:37.208 --> 18:39.458
'cause you two would make
beautiful babies.

18:39.458 --> 18:40.959
- Mom.
- 'Oh, come on.'

18:40.959 --> 18:43.333
Look at him, he's gorgeous,
they're gorgeous.

18:43.333 --> 18:45.167
- 'Okay.'
- 'Yeah.'

18:45.167 --> 18:48.041
[Gustav & The Seasick Sailors
singing "Breakthrough"]

18:48.041 --> 18:50.208
- Ready for another?
- God, yes.

18:50.208 --> 18:52.000
[chuckles]

18:57.542 --> 19:00.125
Hey, it's the new coach.

19:00.125 --> 19:02.000
I should, uh, go say hello,
right?

19:02.000 --> 19:05.500
Oh, no, no, no, honey, honey,
this is our together time.

19:05.500 --> 19:07.959
I know, but it's good
to get on his radar.

19:07.959 --> 19:10.667
Do you know how much
a staff football doctor makes?

19:16.209 --> 19:18.667
Coach Raymond. Hey.

19:18.667 --> 19:20.125
- I'm a huge fan.
- Really?

19:20.125 --> 19:21.708
The way in which
you turned around

19:21.708 --> 19:24.209
that program down there
at Louisiana, coach

19:24.209 --> 19:25.500
nothing short of brilliant.

19:25.500 --> 19:27.625
I don't think Bear Bryant
could have done better.

19:27.625 --> 19:30.167
Flattery will get you a beer.
What did you say
your name was?

19:30.167 --> 19:33.042
Derrick, Derrick Altman,
sports doctor here at Lancer.

19:33.042 --> 19:34.417
'I'm actually working
with the Hellcats right now'

19:34.417 --> 19:36.209
'while I finish up
my fellowship.'

19:36.209 --> 19:38.041
(Red)
'A friend of the Hellcats
is a friend of mine.'

19:38.041 --> 19:39.834
Let me buy you
a cold one, doc.

19:43.167 --> 19:46.750
- Hi, I'm Vanessa Lodge.
- My girlfriend.

19:46.750 --> 19:49.000
- Oh.
- Nice to meet you.

19:49.000 --> 19:51.333
Yeah, I'm, uh,
Hellcats' head coach

19:51.333 --> 19:53.708
so I'm sure we'll be seeing
a lot of each other.

19:53.708 --> 19:55.333
Pleased to meet you, too.

19:55.333 --> 19:58.000
Actually, coach, you two
have a bit of shared history.

19:59.125 --> 20:00.792
- Is that so?
- Yeah.

20:00.792 --> 20:02.167
Yeah, Vanessa here
was a Hellcat

20:02.167 --> 20:04.083
back when you
were a coach.

20:05.250 --> 20:07.625
[chuckles]

20:07.625 --> 20:09.000
Small world.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.625
Yeah. Wouldn't wanna paint it.

20:12.084 --> 20:14.917
I tell you what, uh,
I promised Derrick here a beer

20:14.917 --> 20:16.708
and since
we'll be working together

20:16.708 --> 20:18.917
how about
you sit with me and the boys?

20:18.917 --> 20:21.917
- We can bond.
- It sounds like fun.

20:21.917 --> 20:23.458
It does, doesn't it?

20:26.708 --> 20:29.041
Oh, good Lord.

20:29.041 --> 20:32.000
- Savannah, where's home?
- Millington.

20:32.000 --> 20:33.750
- Oh, Alice?
- Okay, we're..

20:33.750 --> 20:37.209
- Oh, will you look at this?
- No, we're, we're done.

20:37.209 --> 20:39.083
Oh, do you, do you see that?

20:39.083 --> 20:41.792
My daughter here thinks
I can't handle my liquor.

20:41.792 --> 20:43.959
Am I a grown woman or not?

20:43.959 --> 20:45.291
This is your second bottle,
okay?

20:45.291 --> 20:49.375
Lewis...I look like
a grown woman to you?

20:50.625 --> 20:53.875
- Uh, yes, ma'am.
- Hm.

20:53.875 --> 20:54.959
[chuckles]

20:54.959 --> 20:57.084
Alright.
Yeah, have at it.

20:58.166 --> 21:00.000
Actually,
let me get you a trough.

21:00.000 --> 21:01.792
Do not talk to me
in that tone of voice--

21:01.792 --> 21:03.166
Oh, wow,
now you're getting parental--

21:03.166 --> 21:05.084
- I'll rip you a--
- Let's send up a flare, why--

21:05.084 --> 21:06.208
I'm from Millington,
Tennessee.

21:06.208 --> 21:08.167
It's about 12 miles north
from here.

21:08.167 --> 21:11.125
Yeah, the same place,
uh, Justin Timberlake's
from, right?

21:11.125 --> 21:12.917
Oh, I love him.

21:13.834 --> 21:16.041
I would rock that body.

21:18.042 --> 21:20.375
[laughing]

21:22.125 --> 21:24.125
[instrumental music]

21:25.167 --> 21:27.917
Oh, this was
a delightful evening.

21:27.917 --> 21:30.083
I don't want it to end.

21:30.083 --> 21:32.667
Come on, Mom.
You know, I'll just,
I'll walk you to the car.

21:32.667 --> 21:34.208
Is this a sofa bed?

21:34.208 --> 21:37.875
Not a chance in hell.
Yeah, okay.

21:37.875 --> 21:41.167
[music continues]

21:45.625 --> 21:48.000
I can't go home.

21:48.000 --> 21:49.250
I know you get lonely.

21:49.250 --> 21:50.875
I'll-I'll just,
I'll drive you home

21:50.875 --> 21:52.083
I'll tuck you in,
we'll watch a bad movie.

21:52.083 --> 21:53.375
No, really, I can't go home.

21:53.375 --> 21:55.042
I came home from work,
and there is this

21:55.042 --> 21:56.375
big padlock on the front door.

21:56.375 --> 21:59.166
- You got evicted?
- I am not paying
for that car.

21:59.166 --> 22:01.625
Even if I could afford it
on principle.

22:01.625 --> 22:03.166
Car? W-what are you,
what are you talking about?

22:03.166 --> 22:05.500
You remember
that flood upstairs
last winter?

22:05.500 --> 22:07.209
You know the landlord,
Mr. Aziki?

22:07.209 --> 22:09.542
Yes, Mom. I sent in
your rent checks.

22:09.542 --> 22:11.959
Okay, he finally agrees

22:11.959 --> 22:14.500
to fix the water stains
on that kitchen wall.

22:14.500 --> 22:16.458
He wants to paint it eggshell.

22:17.667 --> 22:18.959
So..

22:18.959 --> 22:21.000
The wall has always been sage.

22:21.000 --> 22:23.000
It matches the tablecloth

22:23.000 --> 22:26.959
but Mr. Aziki insists
on painting it a neutral color

22:26.959 --> 22:29.209
because, get this,
it's easier to rent

22:29.209 --> 22:30.917
and I'm still living there.

22:30.917 --> 22:32.875
I mean,
can you imagine the nerve?

22:32.875 --> 22:34.041
So the man raises his voice

22:34.041 --> 22:37.167
and I will not be talked to
with disrespect.

22:37.167 --> 22:39.333
And I pick up that paint can
and then I open the window--

22:39.333 --> 22:42.750
Wait, does this end with you
trashing our landlord's car?

22:42.750 --> 22:45.125
He said some very ugly things.

22:47.167 --> 22:48.708
No! Okay!
Okay, you know what?

22:48.708 --> 22:50.167
- You, you can stay.
- Ah.

22:50.167 --> 22:52.417
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa,
on one condition.

22:52.417 --> 22:54.167
Tomorrow you sit down
with Mr. Aziki

22:54.167 --> 22:55.208
and you fix this on your own.

22:55.208 --> 22:57.125
Oh, how am I supposed
to do that?

22:57.125 --> 22:59.041
I mean, I don't have the money
to fix his stupid car.

22:59.041 --> 23:00.458
You're a big girl,
figure it out.

23:00.458 --> 23:01.750
But I don't have the--

23:01.750 --> 23:03.959
Otherwise you sleep
in a motel.

23:07.167 --> 23:09.542
- Do we have a deal?
- Oh.

23:14.542 --> 23:16.166
Deal.

23:17.750 --> 23:19.209
[sighs]

23:21.750 --> 23:26.041
Savannah!
I was just going to call you.

23:26.041 --> 23:28.291
You were? Why?
Is Charlotte okay?

23:28.291 --> 23:30.542
Doctor say she's fine,
but she's in pain

23:30.542 --> 23:33.125
and you just never know
with a head injury.

23:33.125 --> 23:35.083
Your dad and I
are holding a prayer circle

23:35.083 --> 23:38.000
for her on Saturday
if you would like to come.

23:38.000 --> 23:43.417
- Of course. I'll be there.
- Good, 10 a.m.

23:45.750 --> 23:47.959
Wait, that's our redo time
for qualifiers.

23:47.959 --> 23:50.458
Well, your sister's
not getting a redo.

23:52.084 --> 23:54.750
It's just a prayer, right?

23:54.750 --> 23:56.417
I mean, can't that be done
at any time?

23:56.417 --> 24:00.125
- I-I can make it by noon.
- Just a prayer?

24:00.125 --> 24:01.959
There are a lot of people
coming, Savannah.

24:01.959 --> 24:03.333
Pastor George
is making a special trip

24:03.333 --> 24:06.959
so if this is important
to you, you'll be here.

24:08.167 --> 24:10.083
We do hope
to see you tomorrow.

24:17.458 --> 24:21.084
Hey, hon, it's me.
I hope your day's going well.

24:21.084 --> 24:22.917
I got your message
about picking up dinner

24:22.917 --> 24:24.417
and I just thought that..

24:24.417 --> 24:25.500
[gasps]

24:25.500 --> 24:27.542
Oh, my gosh!

24:27.542 --> 24:31.042
Derrick, I'm gonna kill you.

24:31.042 --> 24:33.500
You know we shouldn't be
spending money on..

24:35.750 --> 24:38.041
...takeout food every night.

24:38.041 --> 24:41.500
So, um, I'm just gonna
pick up some veggies

24:41.500 --> 24:44.125
and make a stir fry

24:44.125 --> 24:47.083
with some buckwheat noodles
like you like.

24:48.125 --> 24:50.500
Okay. Love you.

24:50.500 --> 24:53.542
[instrumental music]

24:55.042 --> 24:56.083
[grunting]

24:56.083 --> 24:57.375
Oops.

24:58.125 --> 25:00.500
Again, Marti, lock your knees.

25:00.500 --> 25:02.042
Okay. Again.

25:02.042 --> 25:05.041
[instrumental music]

25:09.583 --> 25:12.125
Ooh! Oh!

25:12.125 --> 25:15.208
What's with you today?
Focus. Come on.

25:17.250 --> 25:18.583
Help.

25:23.333 --> 25:25.291
Oop, uh!

25:26.542 --> 25:28.041
[grunting]

25:31.333 --> 25:32.959
Who am I kidding?

25:32.959 --> 25:35.084
She's gonna die
a horrible death without me.

25:35.084 --> 25:36.583
What? Who's gonna die
a horrible death?

25:36.583 --> 25:37.708
[sighs]

25:37.708 --> 25:39.167
Who do you think?

25:39.167 --> 25:41.125
Marti, where are you going?

25:42.333 --> 25:45.375
[music continues]

26:01.167 --> 26:04.209
Mr. Aziki, you do realize
by locking my mother out

26:04.209 --> 26:05.125
you've violated the uniform

26:05.125 --> 26:06.917
residential landlord
and tenant acts?

26:06.917 --> 26:08.375
My baby's studying
to be a lawyer.

26:08.375 --> 26:10.875
I could have you arrested
for throwing paint on my car.

26:10.875 --> 26:12.041
We could file suit.

26:12.041 --> 26:14.041
Mutually assured destruction.

26:14.041 --> 26:16.959
But why go to the dark place?

26:19.083 --> 26:20.917
Where'd you get all that cash?

26:20.917 --> 26:22.250
Cash advance.

26:22.250 --> 26:24.500
This should cover the damage,
Mr. Aziki.

26:24.500 --> 26:26.375
Barely.

26:26.375 --> 26:27.834
On one condition, though.

26:27.834 --> 26:29.875
You paint the wall sage,
primer, two coats.

26:29.875 --> 26:32.167
- Sage.
- Mm-hmm.

26:34.375 --> 26:36.084
Agreed.

26:38.417 --> 26:42.042
Thank you, sweetheart.
You really came through.

26:42.042 --> 26:44.209
I, I don't want your thanks.

26:44.209 --> 26:45.041
I want you to pay me back.

26:45.041 --> 26:46.667
I want you to be responsible.

26:46.667 --> 26:49.375
I don't want to have
to save your ass
every day of our lives.

26:49.375 --> 26:51.208
- Got it?
- Got it.

26:51.208 --> 26:55.042
Yeah, so Alice was
saying that you're
gonna get a do-over

26:55.042 --> 26:57.458
for qualifiers?

26:57.458 --> 26:59.041
- She was?
- At dinner.

26:59.041 --> 27:00.667
She said
that the Hellcats are gonna

27:00.667 --> 27:03.667
get another chance
to go in front of the judges.

27:03.667 --> 27:06.667
Um, yeah, yeah, Vanessa tried,
but it, it didn't work out.

27:06.667 --> 27:09.834
Oh, but what about
your scholarship?

27:13.000 --> 27:14.083
I'll figure out something.

27:14.083 --> 27:17.084
Well, if anyone can
figure it out, it's you.

27:24.250 --> 27:27.167
Mom, come on.

27:27.167 --> 27:29.667
Of course, I do.

27:29.667 --> 27:31.667
I'm sorry, but I'm gonna
have to support Charlotte

27:31.667 --> 27:34.041
in my own way.
The squad is depending on me.

27:34.041 --> 27:36.792
[door opens]

27:36.792 --> 27:38.750
Yeah, well,
they're my family, too.

27:39.750 --> 27:41.959
Right now
they're my only family.

27:41.959 --> 27:44.667
I made sure of that.

27:44.667 --> 27:47.084
Mom? Mom?

27:48.167 --> 27:49.750
[scoffs]

27:51.208 --> 27:53.166
Mom trouble?

27:53.166 --> 27:55.166
No, of course not.

27:57.084 --> 27:58.959
- You?
- Same.

28:00.708 --> 28:02.667
- I lied to my mom's face.
- [indistinct]

28:03.000 --> 28:04.959
[chuckles]

28:04.959 --> 28:06.458
You first.

28:07.458 --> 28:09.333
Well, my mom asked
about qualifiers

28:09.333 --> 28:11.792
and I told her
that they weren't happening.

28:12.959 --> 28:14.083
When she finds out..

28:14.083 --> 28:16.875
Yeah, it'll break her heart,
I know.

28:16.875 --> 28:21.250
I feel awful,
but she brings it on herself.

28:21.250 --> 28:24.291
I need to concentrate on me
this one time.

28:24.291 --> 28:25.458
And if she doesn't
respect that

28:25.458 --> 28:27.458
then she deserves
to get shut out.

28:28.792 --> 28:31.542
[instrumental music]

28:32.625 --> 28:35.084
What?

28:35.084 --> 28:36.625
I got shut out.

28:38.125 --> 28:39.417
Yeah?

28:40.291 --> 28:42.167
When I transferred to Lancer

28:42.167 --> 28:44.500
it was a huge betrayal
to my folks.

28:44.500 --> 28:45.625
Why?

28:45.625 --> 28:48.583
Memphis Christian
is my family's legacy school.

28:49.875 --> 28:51.291
My mom and dad met there.

28:51.291 --> 28:54.208
My grandfather spent 15 years
as vice chancellor

28:54.208 --> 28:56.125
and my great-grandmother
was the first woman

28:56.125 --> 28:58.000
ever admitted on campus.

28:58.000 --> 29:00.250
There's some serious pressure.

29:00.250 --> 29:04.125
So I went
...but after my freshman year

29:04.125 --> 29:05.708
I realized I wasn't growing.

29:07.166 --> 29:08.417
My sister and I
were homeschooled

29:08.417 --> 29:10.375
and it just felt
more of the same.

29:10.375 --> 29:11.542
There's a whole world
out there

29:11.542 --> 29:13.708
and I wasn't getting
to experience it.

29:16.208 --> 29:18.000
So without telling them

29:18.000 --> 29:20.417
I filled out
a Lancer application.

29:20.417 --> 29:22.125
The cheer scholarship
gave me the freedom

29:22.125 --> 29:24.333
to tell them no..

29:24.333 --> 29:26.208
...for the first time
in my life.

29:27.917 --> 29:29.417
You're happy, though, right?

29:29.417 --> 29:31.125
You should be glad about that.

29:32.250 --> 29:34.084
Lancer is a secular school.

29:35.041 --> 29:37.084
When I came here,
